# John The Ripper Exercises & Labs
- This repo is for educational/demonstration use only.

**Hands-on password cracking labs** using John the Ripper (Kali Linux VM).  
Includes examples for raw MD5 / SHA1 cracking, `/etc/shadow` unshadowing, `zip2john` usage and sample walkthroughs.

**Author:** MarcusR / [GitHub - CyberMarcR](https://github.com/CyberMarcR)  
**Tools:** John the Ripper, zip2john, rockyou.txt, hash-id.py, Kali Linux

---

## Contents
- [John Basics](john-basics.md) — create a hash, crack with John (MD5 & SHA1)
- [Unshadowing `/etc/shadow`](unshadowing-etc.md) — prepare and crack shadow/passwd extracts
- [Cracking password-protected zip files](zip2john-crack.md) — `zip2john` → `john` → unzip
- `scripts/` — helper scripts used in labs
- `images/` — screenshots of terminal output (see pages above)

---

## Quick demo (example)
**Create MD5 hash:**
```bash
echo -n "password" | md5sum
# 5f4dcc3b5aa765d61d8327deb882cf99  -

